newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: European feeds see nearby soymeal trade in afternoon.
newsitem.headline: European feeds see nearby soymeal trade in afternoon.

text.p: The European meals and feeds market saw some activity in nearby soymeal this afternoon at firmer levels, while business in other products remained slow.

"Calls for a stronger Chicago soymeal futures opening linked to the continuing tight supply situation of soymeal in Europe sparked some activity. The barely changed seller prices and a stronger dollar limited business in other products," one broker said.
Afloat Brazilian soymeal pellets tarded $4 up from yesterday at $307 a tonne cif Rotterdam.
Afloat Argentine soymeal pellets changed hands at between $294 and $286 a tonne cif Rotterdam, depending on position. Nov traded traded up $2 at $290 and Dec at $281.50 a tonne cif.
Argentine sunmeal pellets changed hands at $158 a tonne cif Rotterdam.
EU rapemeal changed hands at 30.25 marks per 100 kg fob lower Rhine for Week 49 delivery, Dec at 29.75 and Feb at 29 marks fob lower Rhine.--KAREL LUIMES +31 20 504 5832
